news.title: Arrest Dreamz Infra India's MD for delay in delivery, refusing refund: NCDRC
news.para: The commission had earlier issued a bailable warrant against Disha Choudhury, the managing director of company Dreamz Infra India Ltd for not complying with its order to appear before it. Left with no option, a bench of Justice Inderjit Singh and Sadhna Shanker directed her arrest.

news.title: Fifteen farmhouses built in protected Aravalis razed after NGT order in Gurugram
news.para: The demolition — following directions of National Green Tribunal (NGT) to get rid of all illegal structures in areas that are under Aravali Notification — was carried out by municipal council of Sohna.

news.title: About 100 buyers get registries at RG Luxury Homes in special camps in Noida
news.para: The camp, held at the project site in Greater Noida West, marked the beginning of the registration process. Authorities have been instructed to organise similar camps in other legacy projects to expedite the handover process.

news.title: JSW Paints to acquire up to 75% stake in Akzo Nobel India for ₹9,446 crore
news.para: JSW Paints has signed a share purchase agreement to acquire up to 74.76% of the paid-up equity share capital of Akzo Nobel India from its two promoter shareholders—Imperial Chemical Industries and Akzo Nobel Coatings International B.V.

news.title: Tiruvallur administration seeks more time to clear 194 houses from lake in Avadi
news.para: The collector's report was filed in response to earlier NGT directions in Aug 2024 and March 2025, when the tribunal took stock of encroachments identified and notices issued to 350 individuals under the Tamil Nadu Protection of Tanks and Eviction of Encroachment Act, 2007.

news.title: Punjab rejigs conversion policy, industrial plots can be used to build hotels, office space
news.para: Renewable energy minister Aman Arora said, "Industrial plots of 1,000 square to 4,000 square yards can now be used for commercial activity, banquet halls, rental housing, office space or housing, institutes, or industrial workers' housing, depending on various categories and the width of roads. It will give relief to developers and investors in the state."

news.title: Blackstone buys $2 billion of CRE loans from Atlantic Union Bankshares
news.para: The loans were bought at a slight discount to their face value, the companies said on Thursday. The loans originated from Sandy Spring Bank, which Atlantic Union bought in a $1.6 billion deal in April.

news.title: Gujarat CM announces uniform house tax of ₹200 annually for PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: An annual house tax assessment rate of Rs 200 has been fixed for four years, starting from the current assessment cycle, for houses constructed with government assistance within the limits of all Gram Panchayats across the state, according to the release.

news.title: Kalpataru IPO subscribed 2.26 times on last day of offer
news.para: The Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) category received 3.12 times subscription, while the portion for non-institutional investors got subscribed 1.31 times. The Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) part received 1.29 times subscription.

news.title: Maharashtra approves ₹5 crore for urban development in merged areas of Pune & Uruli Phursungi
news.para: The decision was taken after a special meeting by the urban development department (UDD) chaired by deputy chief minister and UDD minister Eknath Shinde, stated a press release issued by the department.

news.title: Brookfield to sell Australian senior housing platform Aveo for $2.5 billion
news.para: Since acquiring Aveo in 2019 for an equity value of about A$1.27 billion, Brookfield simplified the platform's customer contracts and invested more than A$500 million across the business.

news.title: Arkade Developers acquires new redevelopment project in Mumbai
news.para: Spread across 1.1 acres, the project offers a saleable area of approximately 86,000 sq ft and an estimated revenue potential of ₹350 crore.

news.title: StayVista raises over ₹40 crore in a round led by JSW Ventures
news.para: StayVista plans to deploy the fresh funds to expand into new geographies, further strengthen their team, and improve customer experience and supply-side strengths.

news.title: Asiana Fund invests ₹50 crore in Flipspaces
news.para: The investment is a part of a recent $35 million funding round, which also saw participation from Synergy Capital Partners, Iron Pillar and Prashasta Seth consortium.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body urges residents of buildings without OCs to apply
news.para: ​​Following the Bombay high court's directives on a Public Interest Litigation and a subsequent Writ Petition, NMMC created a detailed catalogue of non-compliant buildings after an extensive survey.

news.title: No data with Gurugram civic body on 34 defaulters with ₹97 crore property tax dues
news.para: Without the details of the owners, there is little action that the corporation can take to collect this property tax, the principal accountant general pointed out in the report for the audit carried out this Feb.

news.title: BMC slashes Worli tower cost by ₹37 crore as Mumbai activist questions expense
news.para: ​After cancelling the original Rs 525-crore tender, BMC issued a fresh Rs 488-crore tender in May. The biggest cost cut was in the robotic parking system — from Rs 96 crore to Rs 72 crore.

news.title: Fire NOC validity extended to five years in Goa, but experts sceptical
news.para: This, however, has authorities worried as experience shows that many commercial establishments do not maintain firefighting equipment. Recently, the fire department found that the fire prevention mechanism at the Panaji municipal market was defunct.

news.title: Allottees selling off industry plots along Yamuna Expressway for quick profits
news.para: According to officials, a recent survey revealed several cases where allottees, instead of setting up factories, engaged in property trading, undermining the objective of job creation and industrial growth.

news.title: Land pooling offers 10-fold returns to farmers: Lucknow development body VC
news.para: During the inspection, Kumar directed officials to fast-track sector development works and ensure that landowners are made aware of the significant benefits of land pooling.
